Types of Plots used: Line, Relational, Scatter, Histogram, and Regression Plots

Note: all datasets used are available in Seaborn

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Importing Libraries

In[7]:
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
sns.set_style('dark')

Line Plot

In[9]:
# Importing Dataset
flights=sns.load_dataset('flights')                   
flights.head()
Out[9]:
year month passengers
0 1949 Jan 112
1 1949 Feb 118
2 1949 Mar 132
3 1949 Apr 129
4 1949 May 121
In[13]:
flights_feb=flights[flights['month']=='Feb']       # getting all years with passengers in within February Month
flights_feb.head(6)                                # getting sample of data with 6 rows only
Out[13]:
year month passengers
1 1949 Feb 118
13 1950 Feb 126
25 1951 Feb 150
37 1952 Feb 180
49 1953 Feb 196
61 1954 Feb 188
In[15]:
sns.set_style('darkgrid')                                            # colour of grid lines                           
sns.lineplot(x='year',y='passengers',data=flights_feb)               # plotting only flights in February month
plt.title('Number of Passengers in February each Year')
plt.xlabel('Year')
plt.ylabel('Number of Passengers')
plt.show()
In[17]:
plt.figure(figsize=(10,8))                                         # choosing large specific dimension
sns.lineplot(x='year',y='passengers',data=flights,size='month',hue='month')  
# plotting all data with different month colour, different size compared to passengers
plt.show()

In[24]:
# plotting line plot                                       
sns.lineplot(data=fmri,y='signal',x='timepoint',hue='event',style='region')   
# 'hue'  :parameter used for changing colour,    'style' : line type based on 'region column
plt.show()

to separate each graph with each 'event'

Relational Plots

In[157]:
# 'relplot' : For Drawing Relational Plots
sns.relplot(data=fmri,y='signal',x='timepoint',hue='event',kind='line',style='region',col='region',row='event')   
plt.show()

In[34]:
sns.set_style('darkgrid')

Out[34]:
<Axes: xlabel='total_bill', ylabel='tip'>
In[36]:
sns.scatterplot(data=tips,x='total_bill',y='tip',hue='size',size='size',sizes=(10,150),palette='cool')
# 'palette' --> color of dots   ,  'cool' as sequential colour
Out[36]:
<Axes: xlabel='total_bill', ylabel='tip'>
In[38]:

Out[38]:
<Axes: xlabel='total_bill', ylabel='tip'>
In[42]:
sns.relplot(data=tips,x='total_bill',y='tip',hue='time',style='sex',kind='scatter',col='sex',row='day')
plt.show()
In[48]:
sns.regplot(x='total_bill',y='tip',data=tips)
Out[48]:
<Axes: xlabel='total_bill', ylabel='tip'>
In[50]:
sns.regplot(x='size',y='tip',data=tips)
# each time 'size' column increases, 'tip' column increases
Out[50]:
<Axes: xlabel='size', ylabel='tip'>
In[52]:
sns.regplot(x='size',y='tip',data=tips,x_jitter=0.1)   
# 'x_jitter' : for adding spaces between points
Out[52]:
<Axes: xlabel='size', ylabel='tip'>
In[54]:
sns.regplot(x='size',y='tip',data=tips,x_estimator=np.mean)
# calculate mean for each category--> 'size'
Out[54]:
<Axes: xlabel='size', ylabel='tip'>

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

'regplot()' always shows a single relationship, 'lmplot()' combines 'regplot()' with FacetGrid to show multiple fits using hue mapping.

In[61]:
sns.lmplot(x='total_bill',y='tip',data=tips,hue='smoker',col='smoker',row='sex',truncate=False)
Out[61]:
<seaborn.axisgrid.FacetGrid at 0x1b182b78b30>
In[63]:
sns.lmplot(x='total_bill',y='tip',data=tips,hue='smoker',col='smoker',scatter_kws={'s':100,'edgecolor':'blue'},line_kws={'lw':6,'ls':'--'})
Out[63]:
<seaborn.axisgrid.FacetGrid at 0x1b182f355e0>
